The magnificent PEC photocurrent properties of the MgCr-LDH/PS and the corresponding MgCr-LDH nanosheets and hierarchical 3D MgCr-LDH/NP structure were investigated using LSV studies as obtained under dark and visible light illumination in order to legacy the function of photoinduced excitonic charge separation to intensify the net photocurrent as shown in Fig. 6a,b. The photocurrent measurement studies of the series of MgCr-LDH materials were recorded in potential panel of − 1.0 to 1.2 V vs. Ag/AgCl reference electrode using 0.1 M Na2SO4 (pH = 6.5), at scan rate of 10 mV s−1 and converted to reversible hydrogen electrode (RHE) according to the Nernst equation.4E(RHE)=EAg/AgCl+0.197+0.059 pH.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
